  "methods": "<p>DNA from individual <em>Aedes aegypti </em>mosquitoes was extracted and used for genotyping at 50,000 loci distributed along the species genome, using the Axiom Aegypti1 SNP chip (Life Technologies Corporation CAT#550481). </p>\n<p>Files \"all_snps_G3Dryad\" and \"Replicas_SNPchip\" contain all 50,000 SNPs genotyped, prior to filtering. </p>\n<p>File \"50k_SNPs_30_samples_LD_MAF_miss_FINAL\" contain the SNPs after applying filters in Plink 1.9 (https://www.cog-genomics.org/plink/) for linkage disequilibrium (LD: -indep-pairwise 50 10 0.3), minor allele frequency (MAF: -maf 0.1) and missing data (-geno 0.1).</p>",
